sentence: Stock futures were cautiously higher into Tuesday's open as Wall Street sorts through a deluge of corporate earnings and braces for Apple's ( AAPL ) results after today's close.
Before the open, component stocks Proctor & Gamble ( PG ), Merck ( MRK ) and DuPont ( DD ) reported upbeat results, offset by underwhelming results from Caterpillar ( CAT ) and 3M (MMM).

Up next is the FHFA and Case Shiller home price indices, expected to increase 0.5% and 0.2%, respectively in August, followed at 10am ET with October consumer confidence, projected to drop to 101.0 from 104.1 in September.
